                        <p> <hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>ASE 2.&#8212;<name type="person">Private Jos. Oldham</name>, <name type="organization">Co. G, 52d N. Y.</name>; age
                                20; admitted <date type="admit" when="1863-11-23">Nov. 23, 1863</date>.  Died <date type="death" when="1863-12-13">December 13</date>.  <hi rend="italic">Post-mortem</hi> examination: The posterior portion of the epiglottis and pharynx was covered by a diphtheritic membrane; the
                                        cellular tissue of the larynx was &#339;dematous and indurated;
                                        the upper portion of the first and the whole of the third
                                        lobe of the right lung were hepatized; other thoracic and
                                        abdominal organs normal.&#8212;<hi rend="italic"><name type="person" key="245">Ass't Surgeon H. Allen</name>,
                                                <name type="organization" key="190">U. S. A.</name>, <name type="hospital" key="176">Lincoln Hospital</name>, Washington, D.C.</hi>  </p>                        
